text: Gymnothorax ocellatus is a moray eel found in coral reefs in the western Atlantic Ocean.Gymnothorax ocellatus at www.fishbase.org. It was first named by Louis Agassiz in 1831, and is also commonly known as the blackedge moray, Caribbean ocellated moray, conger, ocellated moray, spotted moray, sawtooth moray, white-spotted moray, or yellow cong.Common names for Gymnothorax ocellatus at www.fishbase.org. ==References== ocellatus Category:Fish described in 1831
